OL,3,CMan arrested after suspected hate
OL,4,Ccrime at place of worship
OL,6,FA man has been arrested in connection
OL,7,Fwith a suspected hate crime where a
OL,8,Fthreatening letter and dog faeces were
OL,9,Fdropped inside a Christian place of
OL,10,Fworship.
OL,12,FAvon and Somerset Police said the
OL,13,Fletterbox of the Kingdom Hall of
OL,14,FJehovah's Witnesses in Mart Road,
OL,15,FMinehead, was also damaged with paint.
OL,17,FThe force added that a vehicle was
OL,18,F"also targeted with symbols associated
OL,19,Fwith the far right, that leads us to
OL,20,Fconsider there was a hateful intent".
OL,26,@zD@AOU|D@dO]
